<Group labelreference="L632" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Title" layout="Title">Grobner Basis Method for Parametrizing Matrices</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L634" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Setup global variables and import the example matrix H we are using. Note that we are assuming the file containing H is within the working directory.</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L609" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">restart: with(LinearAlgebra): interface(rtablesize=12):
Digits := 30: 
n := 12: EPS:=10.^(-8):
read &quot;H.m&quot;: # H is 12x12 numeric S-Hadamard matrix to parametrize</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L425" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L8" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal"># Function for checking a numeric 12x12 matrix is S-Hadamard</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L420" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">checkSolutionMatrix := proc(H::Matrix)
global n;
local i, j, ip, sip;
  <Font encoding="UTF-8">printf(&quot;Unimodular Err: %e\134n&quot;, max( seq(seq( abs( abs(H[i,j]) - 1 ) , j=1..n),i=1..n) ));
</Font>  ip := (u,v) -&gt; add( u[i]/v[i], i=1..n );
  <Font encoding="UTF-8">printf(&quot;Hadamard Err: %e\134n&quot;, max( seq(seq( abs( ip(H[i],H[j]) - 0 ) , j=i+1..n),i=1..n) ));
</Font>  sip := (u,v) -&gt; add( u[i]^2/v[i]^2 , i=1..n );
  printf(&quot;S-Hadamard Err: %e&quot;, max( seq(seq( abs( sip(H[i],H[j]) - 0 ) , j=i+1..n),i=1..n) ));
end:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L421" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L422" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">checkSolutionMatrix(H);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="Line Printed Output" layout="Line Printed Output">Unimodular Err: 4.940500e-12
Hadamard Err: 2.859354e-11
S-Hadamard Err: 5.792467e-11</Text-field>
</Output>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L423" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L636" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">The following are variables and functions that we use to help find and update positions of the symbolic matrix based on matrix H.</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L18" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">ind:={ seq(seq( [i,j], i=1..n ),j=1..n) }: # Set of indices of 12x12 matrix</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L24" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L30" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">findPos := proc(H::Matrix, val::complex(float))
global EPS, ind;
  select( pos -&gt; abs(H[pos[1], pos[2]] - evalf(val)) &lt; EPS, ind );
end:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L34" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L82" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">updatePos := proc(H::Matrix, pos::set, val::algebraic)
local pa;
  for pa in pos do
    H[pa[1], pa[2]] := val;
  od:
end:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L653" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Heading 1" layout="Heading 1">A Naive Parametrization</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L638" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">We initialize the symbolic matrix that will become a parametrization of matrix H. We start setting entries that are equal to 1 or -1 in H to the same value in the symbolic matrix Hs.</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L637" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">Hs := Matrix(n,n):</Text-field>
</Input>
