<Group labelreference="L642" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Now we group all remaining entries in H which are not set in Hs yet. We first group all pairs of entries that are not equal to 1, a, w, or w^2 in H by their indices. We then merge each pair of indices with every other pair that shares one of the two indices of the pair. That is, we merge the pairs into a set of three indices. We then merge these triples in a similar way to form sets of 4 indices, and keep repeating this process until we can no longer merge sets of indices. A set of indices of H formed in this way contains all entries in H equal to the same value. By finding all such sets, we determine all unique values of entries in H and all positions of each unique value in the matrix.</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L32" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">al := { w=exp(2*Pi*I/3) , a=H[2,2] }:
alf := evalf(al):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L31" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
