<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Hence, there are 3 independent parameters in Hs as the GB only contains one polynomial. We can replace r by w(eb/a) in Hs, and get the final symbolic matrix derived from matrix H. We also relabel parameter e as c, so that the parameters in the final form of Hs, denoted S, are a,b,c which are unimodular complex numbers.</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L595" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">S := eval(Hs, {r=w*b*c/a, e=c});</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="2D Output" layout="Maple Output"><Equation executable="false" style="2D Output" display=""></Equation></Text-field>
